Requirements
============

  * Python 3.12 or newer
  * Mutagen >= 1.30
  * Click >= 8.0

How to install
==============

We recommend using uv (https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) so you can run
`musync` from any directory without activating an environment.

Windows
-------

  1. Install uv (e.g. from https://docs.astral.sh/uv/getting-started/).

  2. From the project directory:

     > uv tool install -e .

  3. Ensure uv's tool directory is on your PATH (uv usually does this).
     Check with:  uv tool dir
     Then run:    musync --version

  To install into an existing environment (e.g. conda) instead:

     > uv pip install -e . --system

     (Use a Python 3.12+ environment; the project requires Python >= 3.12.)

Linux
-----

  1. Install uv (e.g.  curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh  ).

  2. From the project directory:

     $ uv tool install -e .

  3. Ensure uv's tool directory is on your PATH (see  uv tool dir ).
     Then run:  musync --version

  To install system-wide (as root) with pip:

     $ sudo pip install -e /path/to/musync

  Or into a virtualenv:

     $ python3 -m venv .venv
     $ source .venv/bin/activate
     $ pip install -e .

Configuration
=============

  * Linux:  copy  share/musync.conf  and  share/musync.rules  to  ~/.musync/
    or install to  /etc/  for system-wide config.

  * Windows:  copy  share\musync.conf  and  share\musync.rules  to
    %USERPROFILE%\.musync\  (or the paths shown in  share\musync.conf ).

  Read  share/musync.conf  (or  docs/configuration.md ) for how to configure.
